OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1784285298
OL,3,CBoy, 14, pleads not guilty over
OL,4,Calleged plan to target two mosques
OL,6,FThe court heard the mosque attacks
OL,7,Fwere to take place on August 28 and he
OL,8,Fwas motivated by "an extreme right-
OL,9,Fwing ideology".
OL,11,FHe also allegedly had a plan to cause
OL,12,Fcriminal damage which included
OL,13,F"bricking" and slashing tyres which
OL,14,Fwas nicknamed Operation Terrorise
OL,15,FSutton.
OL,17,FThe boy was remanded to youth
OL,18,Fdetention for his next appearance in
OL,19,Fcustody at the Old Bailey on August 21.
